WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.280
So, I will discuss systemic mastocytosis 2026 updates.

00:00:07.280 --> 00:00:08.680
These are my disclosures.

00:00:08.680 --> 00:00:14.840
So, KIT inhibitors in mastocytosis, currently in 2026, we have midostorin and evapritinib,

00:00:14.840 --> 00:00:20.960
FDA approved for advanced SM, imatinib is FDA approved for KIT, the H16 negative aggressive

00:00:20.960 --> 00:00:26.920
SM, and evapritinib is FDA approved in indolent SM.

00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:30.680
What will happen later this year or early next year could be, bizuclastinib could be

00:00:30.680 --> 00:00:36.160
approved in ISM, indolent SM, smoldering SM, and advanced SM.

00:00:36.160 --> 00:00:39.300
This is the data from midostorin led by Dr. Gottlieb.

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:42.880
What I want to focus on is the median survival patients were treated with midostorin was

00:00:42.880 --> 00:00:44.200
around three years.

00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:46.920
Is there still a role for midostorin in 2026?

00:00:46.920 --> 00:00:52.320
Yes, in patients who have a C-finding and thrombocytopenia or high risk of intracranial

00:00:52.320 --> 00:00:56.840
bleeding, someone on warfarin, for example, otherwise, I think evapritinib is the first

00:00:56.840 --> 00:00:56.840
line.

00:00:56.920 --> 00:01:02.100
During ASH, there was an update on the pathfinder study of evapritinib.

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:08.480
This is the phase two study starting at a dose of 200 milligram, and you will see from

00:01:08.480 --> 00:01:15.040
the update, the median duration of response here is around 57 months, 58 months.

00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:20.380
And when you look at the data after maturing, you will see more CR and CR with incomplete

00:01:20.380 --> 00:01:26.840
hematologic recovery of around 30 percent, and the overall survival of the whole population

00:01:26.840 --> 00:01:33.860
previously treated or treatment naive was around five years, whereas it was not reached

00:01:33.860 --> 00:01:37.780
in patients who were treatment naive.

00:01:37.780 --> 00:01:41.740
Side effect profile with the update, it is what we know about evapritinib, cytopenias,

00:01:41.740 --> 00:01:48.980
you will see in those patients, edema, and there was the cognitive disorder, like difficulty

00:01:48.980 --> 00:01:52.600
naming things, for example, was seen in 18 percent, and it was grade three and around

00:01:52.600 --> 00:01:53.600
5 percent.

00:01:53.600 --> 00:01:54.880
Hair color changes were seen in 17 percent of patients.

00:01:54.880 --> 00:01:55.880
I think that's a good thing.

00:01:55.880 --> 00:01:55.880
Thank you very much.

00:01:56.840 --> 00:01:59.100
I tried to compare Explorer to Pathfinder.

00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:04.440
Explorer was the phase one where the patients had higher doses of evapritinib, and you will

00:02:04.440 --> 00:02:08.980
see with the lower dose, when you start at 200 and then go to 100, when patients achieve

00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:15.140
a response, cognitive effects decreased from 30 to 18 percent, hair color changes went

00:02:15.140 --> 00:02:21.200
down from 26 to 17 percent, CNS bleeding risk was lower from 13 to 3.7 percent.

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:26.760
Also, Pathfinder was addended, there was an amendment to the protocol that patients below

00:02:26.760 --> 00:02:32.740
the, with the platelets below the level of 50, they were not allowed to enroll.

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:35.600
Also diarrhea decreased.

00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:39.320
There was progression in 14 percent of patients, mainly in patients with an associated myeloid

00:02:39.320 --> 00:02:45.220
neoplasm, and the progression was to acute leukemia, and there was a recent poster at

00:02:45.220 --> 00:02:54.560
ASH by Dr. Ben Cransell that showed in vitro mass cells suppress monocyte growth, and when,

00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:56.600
and this suppression is released with ADN.

00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:56.680
Okay.

00:02:56.680 --> 00:03:02.000
So, in the future, we'll see, will second generation kit inhibitors be tolerated when

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:03.260
combined with HMA?

00:03:03.260 --> 00:03:04.920
We don't know the answer yet.

00:03:04.920 --> 00:03:11.140
Evapritinib and indolent SM, we know the data, the dose is 25 milligram, that led to the

00:03:11.140 --> 00:03:17.900
FDA approval, and there was a recent three-year update during ASH, and there were no intracranial

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.800
bleeding seen with the lower doses.

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:22.980
And the cognitive adverse events were reported at 8 percent.

00:03:22.980 --> 00:03:26.600
There were grade one to two LFT abnormalities in 9 percent.

00:03:26.600 --> 00:03:28.260
There were four major changes in 4 percent.

00:03:28.260 --> 00:03:33.720
But what's interesting, 29 percent of patients needed to up titrate to 50 milligram.

00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:38.060
There was another abstract that showed when you follow up, when these patients would follow

00:03:38.060 --> 00:03:42.600
up, there were no kit resistance mutations detected on serial sampling.

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:44.860
What about bisuclastinib, the new kid on the block?

00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:48.600
So it's an oral selective kit inhibitor with minimal brain penetration.

00:03:48.600 --> 00:03:53.720
So there are two studies, the SUMMIT and non-advanced SM, and ISM and smoldering SM, using a dose

00:03:53.720 --> 00:03:56.520
of 100 milligram, which is lower than the dose used in the ADN.

00:03:56.520 --> 00:03:59.940
And the APICS trial in advanced SM, which is 150 milligram.

00:03:59.940 --> 00:04:04.140
So during ASH, we had an update on the SUMMIT and ISM and SSM, around six or seven percent

00:04:04.140 --> 00:04:06.300
of the patients had smoldering SM.

00:04:06.300 --> 00:04:10.200
And the trial met its endpoint of improved symptoms.

00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:15.240
So the placebo, there was a decrease of 15 points in the symptom score, whereas it was

00:04:15.240 --> 00:04:18.800
24 points with bisuclastinib.

00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:22.600
When I try to compare, it's always like from fellowship, don't compare trials head to head,

00:04:22.600 --> 00:04:26.440
like if they are not randomized, but if you look at the graphs, maybe there is an earlier

00:04:26.440 --> 00:04:29.820
response, earlier improvement in symptoms with bisuclastinib.

00:04:29.820 --> 00:04:34.740
When you look at the symptom improvement, maybe also when you compare it to evapritinib,

00:04:34.740 --> 00:04:41.120
maybe there's a little bit more improvement in the cognitive symptoms that happen in ISM.

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:43.660
You will see very nice waterfall plots.

00:04:43.660 --> 00:04:47.560
What's interesting in evapritinib and bisuclastinib, the objective measures, they improve much

00:04:47.560 --> 00:04:49.440
more than you see with the symptoms.

00:04:49.440 --> 00:04:50.440
So that's interesting.

00:04:50.440 --> 00:04:56.360
We don't know the reason why, but very nice improvement in mast cell burden, tryptase,

00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:57.360
epinephrine.

